      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <updateDate>2017-05-25T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2017-09-25T16:57:47Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Expresses the sense of the House of Representatives that:</p> <UL> <LI>Congress should establish a federal reapportionment system that would create compact and contiguous congressional districts that, to the greatest extent possible, follow geographic boundaries and county lines; <LI>congressional districts should not favor or disfavor an incumbent or political party; <LI>congressional districts should adhere to the existing standards of equal population; and <LI>the highest court of each state should have the power to reject congressional district maps that do not meet the above criteria. </LI> </UL>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2017-05-25</actionDate>
